Day 1: CSS Basics (Start Here 🔥)

Today you will learn:

What CSS is
How to connect CSS to HTML
3 ways to write CSS
Basic selectors
Simple styling
1. What is CSS?

CSS = Cascading Style Sheets

👉 It is used to style HTML pages:

Colors
Fonts
Layout
Spacing
Design
Example:

HTML = structure
CSS = beauty/design

2. How to Add CSS (3 Ways)
1. Inline CSS (Not preferred)
<h1 style="color: red;">Hello</h1>

👉 Used only for testing

2. Internal CSS

Inside <style> tag

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        h1 {
            color: blue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Welcome</h1>

</body>
</html>
3. External CSS (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥)
Step 1: HTML file
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>

<h1>Hello CSS</h1>

</body>
</html>
Step 2: style.css
h1 {
    color: green;
}
3. CSS Syntax
selector {
    property: value;
}

Example:

p {
    color: blue;
    font-size: 20px;
}
4. CSS Selectors (VERY IMPORTANT)
1. Element Selector
h1 {
    color: red;
}

👉 Applies to all <h1>

2. Class Selector
<p class="text">Hello</p>
.text {
    color: green;
}
3. ID Selector
<p id="para1">Hello</p>
#para1 {
    color: blue;
}
5. Basic Styling Properties
Color
h1 {
    color: red;
}
Background Color
body {
    background-color: lightgray;
}
Font Size
p {
    font-size: 18px;
}
Text Alignment
h1 {
    text-align: center;
}



1. What is CSS?

👉 CSS is used to style HTML elements like color, layout, and design.

2. Difference between inline, internal, external CSS?
Type	Usage
Inline	inside tag
Internal	inside <style>
External	separate .css file
3. Difference between class and id?
Class	ID
Can be reused	Unique
.class	#id
4. What is selector?

👉 Selector is used to target HTML elements.
